## 2. CSS Modules Styles (`ComponentName.module.css`)

### Base Template

```css
.root {
  /* CSS variables for theming (use semantic tokens only) */
  --cv-component-name-bg: var(--color-background-default);
  --cv-component-name-color: var(--color-text-default);

  /* Base styles */
  background: var(--cv-component-name-bg);
  color: var(--cv-component-name-color);
}

/* Variants */
.alternative {
  --cv-component-name-bg: var(--color-fill-common-brand);
  --cv-component-name-color: var(--color-text-inverted);
}

/* States */
.root:hover {
  /* hover styles */
}

.root:focus {
  outline-offset: 4px;
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-border-interactivity-default);
}

.root:disabled {
  cursor: default;
  opacity: 0.5;
}

/* Boolean modifiers */
.fullWidth {
  width: 100%;
}

.disabled {
  cursor: default;
  opacity: 0.5;
}
```

### CSS Modules Conventions

- **Root class**: Always use `.root` as the primary class
- **Variants**: Separate classes applied via `styles[variant]`
- **Modifiers**: Classes like `.fullWidth`, `.disabled`, `.checked`
- **CSS Variables**: Use the `--cv-` prefix for component variables
- **Fallbacks**: Always include fallback values in `var()` → `var(--token, #fallback)`
- **Design tokens**: Use existing tokens (see "Semantic tokens only" below)
- **CSS nesting**: Native nesting can be used for states (`:hover`, `:focus`, etc.)

### Semantic tokens only — never use primitives

**Rule:** In CSS modules, always use variables from **semantic** design tokens. Never reference **primitive** tokens directly. Semantic tokens are defined in `src/styles/design-system-tokens/design-system-tokens.css` and provide meaning (e.g. "default background", "brand border"); primitives are raw values (e.g. "brand dark 50", "size 16") and are an implementation detail.

**Do NOT use (primitives):**
- `--size-*` (e.g. `--size-4`, `--size-16`, `--size-24`)
- `--brand-light-*`, `--brand-dark-*` (e.g. `--brand-dark-50`, `--brand-light-20`)
- `--neutrals-*` (e.g. `--neutrals-black-80`, `--neutrals-light-10`)
- `--system-error-*`, `--system-success-*`, `--system-warning-*`, `--system-info-*` (e.g. `--system-error-50`)
- `--interactivity-states-*`, `--gradients-*`, `--font-family-*`, `--font-weight-*`

**DO use (semantic tokens):**
- **Colors:** `--color-background-*`, `--color-border-*`, `--color-icons-*`, `--color-text-*`, `--color-fill-*`  
  Examples: `--color-text-default`, `--color-background-default`, `--color-fill-common-brand`, `--color-border-interactivity-default`, `--color-icons-brand`
- **Spacing:** `--spacing-xs`, `--spacing-s-exception`, `--spacing-m`, `--spacing-l`, `--spacing-xl`, `--spacing-xxs-exception`, `--spacing-larger-*`
- **Radii:** `--corner-radius-xs`, `--corner-radius-s`, `--corner-radius-m`, `--corner-radius-l`, `--corner-radius-xl`, `--corner-radius-xxl`
- **Typography:** `--font-size-*`, `--line-height-*` (e.g. `--font-size-body-m-default`, `--line-height-body-m-default`)
- **Icons:** `--icon-size-xs`, `--icon-size-s`, `--icon-size-m`, `--icon-size-l`, `--icon-size-xl`

**Example — correct (semantic):**
```css
.root {
  background: var(--color-background-default);
  color: var(--color-text-default);
  padding: var(--spacing-m);
  border-radius: var(--corner-radius-s);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
}
```

**Example — wrong (primitive):**
```css
.root {
  background: var(--neutrals-white-00);        /* avoid: use --color-background-default */
  color: var(--neutrals-black-80);             /* avoid: use --color-text-default */
  padding: var(--size-16);                     /* avoid: use --spacing-m */
  border-radius: var(--size-8);                 /* avoid: use --corner-radius-s */
  border-color: var(--brand-dark-50);           /* avoid: use --color-border-brand or --color-fill-common-brand */
}
```

